<div id="pf5a5d" class="pf w7e h360" data-page-no="5a5d"><div class="pc pc5a5d w7e h360"><div class="t m3d23 x9c h43 y15a9 ff9 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4sisfifftg,.. </div><div class="t m287 xc5 h65 y18b2 ff6 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath Afternoon </div><div class="t m5f7 xc h63 y31b0 ff1 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 13 </div><div class="t m5 x41 h63 y32fb ff1 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">î˜‰</div><div class="t maea x57 h63 y31b0 ff1 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">September 19-25 </div><div class="t m9d x6c hbc y2f24 ff1 fs30 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rebirth Is Renewal </div><div class="t mbcb xc5 h51 y122 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">READ FOR THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Titus 3. </div><div class="t m517 x53 h51 y16b0 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: &quot;Not by works of righteousness which </div><div class="t ma1e x53 h51 y2b7 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">we have done, but according to his mercy he saved us, by </div><div class="t m62b x53 h51 y128d ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the washing of regeneration, and renewing of the Holy </div><div class="t m1bd1 x53 h51 yea2 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ghost&quot; (Titus 3:5). </div><div class="t m1678 x49 h51 y1fa2 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">KEY THOUGHT: </div><div class="t m5af x2e h24 y8bb ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Spiritual rebirth by faith and daily living </div><div class="t m736 xc5 h24 y1ca7 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by faith in Jesus Christ result in the power to follow the </div><div class="t me9a xc5 h24 y68a ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">inspired practical counsel given by Paul. </div><div class="t mce9 x49 h51 ydb9 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">PAUL CONCLUDES HIS INSTRUCTION TO TITUS. </div><div class="t m453 x14a h24 yaf1 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In </div><div class="t m60f xc5 h24 yeaa ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the concluding chapter of his Epistle to Titus, Paul reempha-</div><div class="t m140 xc5 h24 y1592 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sizes the importance of exemplary living. In his relationships </div><div class="t m625 xc5 h24 y440 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with secular authorities the Christian should not only be above </div><div class="t mb91 x34 h24 yed0 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reproach, but should &quot;be ready to do whatever is good&quot; (verse </div><div class="t m647 xc5 h24 y1dd9 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1, NIV). </div><div class="t m73f x49 h24 y1403 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When we were living in habitual sin, we were ruled by our </div><div class="t m27e xc5 h24 y157b ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">passions and in constant conflict with our fellow human be-</div><div class="t m437 xc5 h24 y9c2 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ings. Then came rebirth and renewal by the inner saving work </div><div class="t m17b xc5 h24 y1e6c ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of the Holy Spirit. The power to live as God instructs is </div><div class="t m792 x34 h24 y17dd ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">provided by the saving grace of Christ bestowed upon us by </div><div class="t m2b0 xc5 h24 y1e4 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Holy Spirit. Salvation through Christ not only fits us for </div><div class="t m33e xc5 h24 y7e7 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">worthy citizenship on earth, it makes us &quot;heirs according to </div><div class="t m464 xc5 h24 y91f ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the hope of eternal life&quot; (verse 7). </div><div class="t m296 x49 h24 y628 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Titus 3 provides one of Scripture&apos;s clearest statements of </div><div class="t m863 xc5 h24 y11f2 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">salvation by grace resulting in good works. </div><div class="t m149f xc5 h24 y14e1 ff4 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">90 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
